It's very quiet here, very poetic.

278
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:53,440
It's wonderful to pass by

279
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,679
these little monuments.

280
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:56,759
It allows me to momentarily

281
00:14:56,759 --> 00:14:59,320
detach from the reality.

282
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,480
And every time I see the inscriptions
on these monuments,

283
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,759
I would feel

284
00:15:03,759 --> 00:15:04,840
like I'm reading

285
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,000
a miniature novel.

286
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,000
I would think about

287
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,639
what these people did in life,

288
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:12,039
and what kind of lives they went through.

289
00:15:12,039 --> 00:15:13,399
When they were in Macau,

290
00:15:13,399 --> 00:15:15,799
which places they had been to.

291
00:15:15,799 --> 00:15:17,519
And I would wonder

292
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:18,799
who wrote these loving inscriptions

293
00:15:18,799 --> 00:15:20,879
for them.

294
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,480
Every time I feel upset, I would come here.

295
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,720
If you stand at the end of life,

296
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,600
looking back in life,

297
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,240
you might

298
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,080
let go many things

299
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:37,200
you can't figure out.

300
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:45,159
All the monuments here
date back to the 19th century.

301
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:56,320
Two months six days.

302
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,879
So he only

303
00:15:59,879 --> 00:16:01,840
existed in this world

304
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:03,960
two months and six days.

305
00:16:04,799 --> 00:16:07,200
He was a little baby.

306
00:16:10,559 --> 00:16:14,039
When I first saw him, I was feeling sad

307
00:16:14,039 --> 00:16:16,639
just like you.

308
00:16:16,639 --> 00:16:19,320
I can't help worrying about him.

309
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,679
He's so small, so soft,

310
00:16:21,679 --> 00:16:24,200
lying here all alone.

311
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,720
Must be feeling scared.

312
00:16:27,399 --> 00:16:28,519
So every time I come here,

313
00:16:28,519 --> 00:16:30,320
I'd stand here for a while

314
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,360
to talk to him.

315
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,384
Let's go.

316
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:50,240
George Chinnery.

317
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,840
You know this person?

318
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,840
He had a great impact on Chinese oil painting.

319
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,320
He is also one of the descendants

320
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:58,919
who brought oil painting to China.

321
00:16:58,919 --> 00:17:01,279
Really?

322
00:17:01,279 --> 00:17:03,399
Compared to Giuseppe Castiglione's paintings.

323
00:17:03,399 --> 00:17:04,640
Because Giuseppe Castiglione

324
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:07,039
focused on depicting noble life,

325
00:17:07,039 --> 00:17:08,079
but his paintings

326
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:10,119
are all of ordinary people among the masses.

327
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:11,279
All from

328
00:17:11,279 --> 00:17:12,480
the ordinary life,

329
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,480
very touching.

330
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:15,640
Because of him,

331
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,000
the customs and culture of the coastal areas
of 19th-century China

332
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,440
could be recorded.

333
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,920
He kept a record of this land

334
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,440
until he died.

335
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,720
What do you think

336
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,799
was the reason

337
00:17:35,799 --> 00:17:37,960
he stayed in Macau?

338
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,640
Maybe

339
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,920
he felt a sense of belonging here.

340
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:45,039
There were ties that bound him

341
00:17:45,039 --> 00:17:47,160
or people he couldn't bear to leave.

342
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,720
So, what's

343
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,200
the story behind it?

344
00:17:53,519 --> 00:17:56,960
It must be a very beautiful love story.

345
00:18:04,759 --> 00:18:06,680
After staying here for a little while,

346
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:08,960
I've really calmed down.

347
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:12,119
As you slowly walk around here, you'll realize

348
00:18:12,119 --> 00:18:13,559
that those things we long for

349
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:16,799
don't seem that important anymore.

350
00:18:16,799 --> 00:18:19,359
Everyone is born to die.

351
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:21,079
So when we are alive,

352
00:18:21,079 --> 00:18:23,559
let's enjoy and be unrestrained,

353
00:18:23,559 --> 00:18:25,160
considering our lives to be

354
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,079
a huge amusement park.

355
00:18:27,079 --> 00:18:28,599
Don't expect us to be perfect

356
00:18:28,599 --> 00:18:30,519
at everything we do.

357
00:18:30,519 --> 00:18:34,200
After all, life is all about experience.

358
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,200
Sometimes, just

359
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,680
look down to watch the ants moving house,

360
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,440
or look up at

361
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:41,599
the birds flying across the sky.

362
00:18:41,599 --> 00:18:45,119
And feel the moment, that's enough.

363
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:14,720
<i>After reading this,</i>

364
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,839
<i>if she had only suspected</i>

365
00:19:16,839 --> 00:19:18,119
<i>that Mrs. Xun's death in her previous life</i>

366
00:19:18,119 --> 00:19:19,880
<i>was related to her husband…</i>

367
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:23,359
Meng.

368
00:19:24,839 --> 00:19:26,319
Can you lower the volume

369
